# Vision Specification

## Purpose

This document defines why CAP Market exists and what it is working toward. It expands on the Vision reference in **PH-000 Master Specification**.

---

# Vision

To become Zambia's most trusted neighborhood food marketplace by making it remarkably easy for every family to purchase healthy food.

---

# Mission

To make healthy food affordable, accessible, and convenient while serving every customer with honesty, excellence, and care.

---

# Core Values

**Abundance**
Families should have access to plentiful, quality food.

**Integrity**
Prices are honest. Weights are accurate. Promises are fulfilled.

**Stewardship**
Food, money, inventory, and relationships are carefully managed.

**Excellence**
Every package, order, and interaction reflects quality.

**Simplicity**
The easiest solution is usually the best solution.

**Service**
People matter more than transactions.

---

# Scope Note

This document defines vision, mission, and values only. Brand identity (logo, color, typography) belongs in a future PH-002 Brand Specification, to be written when those decisions are actually needed for design work.

